President Donald Trump issued an Executive Order invoking section 1318(a) of title 19, United States Code, to allow the Secretary of the Treasury to extend deadlines for importers suffering financial hardship due to COVID-19. The order aims to provide additional authority to respond to the national emergency caused by the outbreak of coronavirus disease (COVID-19) in the United States. The Secretary is directed to consider taking appropriate action to temporarily extend deadlines for importers' estimated payments, excluding those assessed under specific sections of title 19, United States Code. The letter was addressed to the Speaker of the House.